Question 9: Use IRF plots to confirm your causality conclusions

In [83]:
irf = results.irf(10)
irf.plot(orth = False)
pyplot.show()

Based on the plots shown above, it is evident that the 0 line falls outside the 95% confidence interval for some of the plots. This implies that the null hypothesis, which suggests the absence of Granger causality, can be rejected. The plots that reject this null hypothesis are consistent with the results obtained from the Granger causality tests discussed earlier. Therefore, our conclusion is valid.
